	<h3><Devicon @size="35" @type="docker" /> Using SurrealDB Nightly with Docker</h3>
	<p>To use SurrealDB Nightly with Docker, you can use the <code>nightly</code> tag. This script securely downloads the latest version for the platform and CPU type. It installs SurrealDB into the <code>C:\Program Files\SurrealDB</code> folder, falling back to a user-specified folder if necessary. The following command will attempt to install the nightly version. You can re-run this command daily to ensure you are running the latest build of SurrealDB.</p>
